# 2. お正月配信に向けて！

Airi: Nice work, everyone! I'm glad that our final stream of the year went as well as it did.
Minori: “New Year's Eve With MORE MORE JUMP!” was a huge success!
Minori: I'd love to make my own soba noodles again! Especially since they ended up being so yummy!
Haruka: Still, we got a lot of viewers this time around. I have to think that your commercial did the trick again for us, Shizuku.
Shizuku: Hehe. That certainly would be nice.
Airi: Let's keep up the momentum starting tomorrow when the new year begins.
Shizuku: Yes, I agree!
KAITO: You all sound very excited about the upcoming year.
Len: Things might be a little hard right now, but I'm sure you girls will find a way to overcome this obstacle.
Airi: Anyway, let's switch gears and start preparing for our next stream!
Haruka: Even though we have New Year's Day off, we'll be streaming on the second. So, we'll need to get everything in order for that.
Airi: Yeah, about that... I thought we could do some extra segments. What do you guys think?
Shizuku: That sounds wonderful! After all, we want everyone to have as much fun as possible.
Minori: But what kinds of extra segments should we do?
Haruka: We're only just now planning them, so we probably won't be able to do anything too involved...
MEIKO: Actually, what do you already have planned for your stream on the second?
Haruka: Let's see... We're going to draw our fortunes using the omikuji boxes we made, and make the New Year's dishes our fans request and have a little feast together. It should be pretty festive.
Miku: Wow! That sounds like such a fun New Year's stream!
Airi: It is important to do seasonal stuff for these kinds of streams.
Rin: Then, does that mean your extra segments should also have a New Year's feel to them?
KAITO: A New Year's feel...
KAITO: In that case, what if you did another stream about New Year's games?
Shizuku: Another stream about New Year's games?
KAITO: Yes, because we heard that the one you did last year went very well. You may have some new fans watching, so it could be good to do another one.
Haruka: It did go pretty well last time... But we sort of landed on trying not to do anything too similar to what we've already done.
Airi: Right. But...
Airi: I see nothing wrong with that idea! It should be fun for everyone, as long as we change up which games we play.
Haruka: Yeah, good point.
KAITO: Then, it's settled! Your extra segments will be another round of New Year's games!
Shizuku: In that case, let's start deciding which games we're going to play, shall we?
Airi: We have a long list of options. But the ones that would make our New Year's stream fun for everyone would be...
Minori: Let's see... We played Karuta and Fukuwarai last time... So, for this stream, what if we made mochi together? We could take turns using the pestle!
Airi: I'm not sure many people would count making mochi as a New Year's game...
Haruka: Also, even if we started looking now, I doubt we'd be able to find a proper mortar and pestle in time.
Minori: Right... I thought it was a good idea, since we didn't get a chance to last time...
Minori: Wait, actually... What if we played a true-to-life version of Fukuwarai?
Shizuku: A true-to-life version?
Minori: Yeah! People on social media have been talking about how you can take pictures of each other and make cutouts using them!
Rin: Whoa! That sounds really fun!
Haruka: Yeah. And it would be a fresh take on something we've already done, so we could have a lot of fun with it.
Airi: Then, I'll put true-to-life Fukuwarai on the list. What else can we play...?
Minori: Hmm... Fukuwarai is definitely a good idea...
Shizuku: But nothing else seems to fit the bill.
KAITO: Well... Playing with spinning tops and kites would be fun, but they're missing that extra something...
Haruka: At least one more game would be nice. Ideally, something that involves us competing against each other, since everyone watching could try to guess who's going to win...
Airi: Yeah... But we also don't have a lot of time...
Airi: Alright, I'll try finding something tomorrow!
Minori: Find? What do you mean?
Airi: As it so happens, I'm gonna go check out the New Year's sales with Ena tomorrow. I'll try seeing if the toy stores and stuff have anything we can use.
KAITO: Right... A toy store could provide you with some new insights...
KAITO: So, Airi, would it be possible for me to join you tomorrow?
Airi: Huh?
KAITO: Seeing what each store carries may help me come up with a good idea.
KAITO: And I'd like to do what I can to help you all shine as brightly as possible when you do play these games!
Airi: Yes, you're absolutely welcome to join us! But I won't be able to talk to you much, since I'm gonna be there with my friend. If you're okay with that...
KAITO: Of course! I'll take quick peeks while staying hidden in your pocket!
Airi: Sounds good. Then, I'll see you tomorrow!
Airi: Let's do our best to make our New Year's stream a good one!
Minori: Yeah!
